# SPARSH DESIGN - Luxury Fashion Boutique 👗

SPARSH DESIGN is a **full MERN stack luxury fashion boutique website**, built to deliver a modern, responsive, and elegant shopping experience. It includes both user and admin interfaces with real-time updates, categorized collections, and interactive animations.

---

## 🚀 Features

### 🛍️ User Side

* Beautifully designed homepage with **hero banners** and **animated sections**.
* View **collections** (bridal, kidswear, custom designs, etc.) with categorized browsing.
* **Gallery** section displaying real-time image updates.
* **Book Appointment** for personalized styling.
* Mobile-friendly responsive layout.

### 🧑‍💼 Admin Side

* **Secure authentication** for admin login.
* Admin can **upload, categorize, and manage images**.
* Real-time updates to the **Gallery component** using Socket.IO.
* Clean, modern dashboard interface.

---

## 🧩 Tech Stack

**Frontend:** React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion, ShadCN UI
**Backend:** Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, Mongoose
**Real-Time Updates:** Socket.IO
**Authentication:** JSON Web Token (JWT)
**Hosting:** Vercel (Frontend) & Render (Backend)

---

## 🗂️ Folder Structure

```
SPARSH-DESIGN/
│
├── frontend/                # React + Vite Frontend
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/      # Reusable UI Components
│   │   ├── pages/           # Page-level Components
│   │   ├── assets/          # Images, icons, etc.
│   │   ├── App.jsx          # Main React Component
│   │   └── main.jsx         # Entry Point
│   ├── package.json
│   ├── tailwind.config.js
│   └── vite.config.js
│
├── backend/                 # Express + MongoDB Backend
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── models/          # Mongoose Schemas
│   │   ├── routes/          # API Routes
│   │   ├── controllers/     # Logic for Routes
│   │   └── server.js        # Main Server File
│   ├── .env
│   └── package.json
│
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

### 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Gokul11271/SPARSH-DESIGN.git
cd SPARSH-DESIGN
```

### 2️⃣ Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend
npm install
```

Create a `.env` file in the backend root:

```
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
PORT=5000
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
```

Start the server:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Server runs on **[http://localhost:5000](http://localhost:5000)** 🚀

### 3️⃣ Frontend Setup

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

Access frontend on **[http://localhost:5173](http://localhost:5173)** 💫

